= Academia

My primary research is side-information assisted +Compressive Sensing (CS)+. We (in collaborate with [https://sites.google.com/site/researchbyzhang Dr. Zhilin Zhang]) have developed advanced Bayesian learning algorithms --- the [https://sites.google.com/site/researchbyzhang/biocs BSBL] framework. I apply these algorithms on Direction-of-Arrival (DOA) estimation, radar imaging and tracking. We also applied CS as a /low-complexity, low-power, robust/ data compression method in bio-signals (ECG, EEG, PPG, etc.) telemonitoring applications.

My current hack-a-project is building advanced and yet small-form-factor +Electrical Impedance Tomograpgy (EIT)+ prototyping hardware at [http://bme.fmmu.edu.cn Dept. of Biomedical Enegineering, FMMU]. And yes, CS technology plays a important role in data acquisition !

I am also a big electronic fan in amatuer radio (HackRF, GNURadio), homebrew PCB (Kicad, Cadsoft Eagle), embedded platforms (ARM cortex-M series, Xilinx FPGAs, and Labview) and Bluetooth technology (Roving Networks RN-42, Nordic nrf51822).  An novel *DCR* (Detect and Communication enabled RADAR) is building on the way, with *Dr. Hongqi Fan*.

